The Telegraph - Calcutta
 1st meet from Sept. 1
New Delhi: The 2004-05 Amby Valley PGAI Tour will begin with the Rs 10-lakh Hyundai-TNGF Open at the Cosmo-TNGF Golf Course in Chennai from September 1. The second tournament of the Southern Swing, incorporating four events and a total prize purse of Rs 40 lakh, will be played at the MGC Golf Links, Chennai, from September 7-10. The southern metropolis will also host the third meet in-a-row when the prestigious Hindu Open tees off from September 15 at the Cosmo-TNGF Course. The golfing caravan then moves to the Garden City of Bangalore for the Hero Honda Open South, which forms the last leg of the Southern Swing. The Bangalore Golf Club will host the four-day meet from September 21-24. (PTI)  Copyright 
